description: Cliff faces a shocking revelation about his past, the Doom Patrol meets Coagula, and Dorothy Spinner signs on with the Wild Girls.
name: The Fox and the Crow

description: With Starfire a captive of the Combine, Nightwing and Flash rush to find her in "Back On Track, Chapter 3: Into The Underworld". Part 3 of 4, continued from the previous issue. Story continues next issue.
name: Back On Track Part 3 of 4: Into the Underworld

description:
Reign of the Supermen tie-in. "Death City!" Guest-starring Superman, Superboy, Supergirl (Matrix) and Steel. Hal returns from his ordeal in space to find Coast City destroyed. With everything he cared about gone, Green Lantern faces the culprits responsible - the sinister Cyborg Superman and the immensely powerful Mongul. Steel and Supergirl have already fallen, is Green Lantern next? Don't miss the tale that changes Hal Jordan's life forever!

Notes:

  • Story continues from Superman: The Man of Steel #26.
  • Superman continues in Superman #82.
name: Death City
What Price Honor?; Meant for Each Other; Those Who Sit and Wait; Say it With Powers; The Book of Equals

description: It's Green Lantern John Stewart vs. Hal Jordan, Kilowog, Flash, Power Girl, Martian Manhunter and Guy Gardner! But even if John saves the Mosaic from this combined might, he won't stop the aliens from taking back their cities and destroying the Mosaic entirely.
name: Get Used to It

description: Tracking down the man who hired Deadline to attack the Netherworld, Hawkman finds himself challenged by Green Lantern, who's out to learn just who this latest incarnation of Hawkman really is, leading to a three-way battle with Meta-Tech and its battle-armored agent, Marauder.
name: Dead End

description:
John Constantine takes a break in an issue that spotlight his ex-love, Kit. Find out what happened to the love of Constantine's life after she walked out on him and returned home...and how she plans on dealing with her decisions.

Note: Apart from his silhouette on the cover, John Constantine does not appear in this issue, rather it follows his ex-lover Kit.
name: Heartland

description: Having narrowly escaped the hangman's noose, Hex sets out with a dead friend to learn the secret of the Mojo Man's travelling freak show.
name: The Resurrectionist

description: The League is caught between a super-powered alien race, Earth's governments and a seemingly helpless pair of interstellar refugees. Picking a side in the fight isn't easy...especially when the enforcer turns out to be Captain Atom!
name: Do the Right Thing

description: The League is ambushed in their headquarters by bizarre terrorists who intend to destroy them. Taken by surprise, the heroes just may fall before their foes.
name: Ambush

description:
Death in the Caribbean!

Knightquest: The Search begins, following the adventures of Bruce Wayne. Wayne is joined by Green Arrow, Gypsy and Bronze Tiger as they form a Task Force to search the island of Santa Prisca for Robin's missing father.
name: Knightquest: The Search

description:
Hide the remote control and make the cable company yank the line out of the wall! The Kid has discovered the power of TV, and the airwaves are no longer safe!

Kid Eternity discovers the power and glory of television.
name: Eating Pop Porn

description: Myrwann relives events from the late 19th century when he was a literary outcast shunned by the staid and morally uptight Victorians.
name: Reflections

description:
The Legion's been buried alive by Mordru and only Devlin and the White Witch remain to face the evil sorcerer! Weakened and battered, Mysa must confront her past to defeat her estranged, abusive husband before he mystically remakes the entire galaxy.

Devlin O'Ryan stands off against Mordru to rescue his buried comrades. Mordru's undead army are defeated.

All the Legionnaires want is some rest and relaxation while staying at the Green Lotus Inn in the Atlantis Dome, but that's when the Devil-Fish attack.

Some members of the Legion of Super-Heroes visit Atlantis, which has recently taken to tourism.
name: Devils In The Deep

description: The Metal Men return...in a story that will shock new and regular DC readers alike. The SUPERMAN #75 creative team of Mike Carlin, Dan Jurgens and Brett Breeding bring this action-packed 4-issue miniseries to life and answer some shocking questions that were first hinted at years ago in the pages of SUPERMAN. The adventure begins when a strange meteor crashes on Earth, and Doctor Will Magnus, creator of the Metal Men, reluctantly deploys his robotic creations to retrieve it. But another party is also interested in the meteor, and won't hesitate to destroy the Metal Men to gain possession of it. In a devastating attack against Magnus Robotics, a secured chamber on Level 12 is forced open. What the Metal Men find inside shakes the team to the core, as secrets Magnus has long kept are revealed, and all that the Metal Men had previously understood about their origins is challenged. By this story's end, those revelations will have forever altered the team.
name: Thanks for the Memories!

description: Metamorpho's search for the Orb of Ra ends in Casablanca, where he must battle one of his own kind to save the life of his son! But to this elemental menace, the problems of two people don't amount to a hill of beans in this crazy world!
name: Chemical Imbalance

description: More heads tumble free of shoulders as Dian becomes enmeshed in the Face's machinations, even as Wesley unearths more clues about the identity of the master assassin.
name: The Face: Act Three

description:
An American Tale, but one with a twist! Meet Prez Rickard, elected to the office of the Presidency in 1972! But how exactly does his victory tie into the plans of the mysterious Boss Smiley? "World's End" part 4.

An Asian man, not yet met in the inn, tells the tale of Prez Rickard. Teenage President of USA from an alternate Earth.

Outer story (pgs 1, 2, 24):

  • Penciller: Bryan Talbot
  • Inker: Mark Buckingham

Inner story (pgs 3-24):

  • Penciller/Inker: Michael Alfred
name: Worlds' End, Part 4: The Golden Boy

description: Shrieking pillows, a grinding mattress, a rock star, a look-alike lost love, and a nasty stain...all in "In Bed with Shade." Take a shower!
name: In Bed With Shade

description: Part 1 of 5. Someone has tampered with time and wiped out the Romulan Empire! With the aid of the Guardian of Forever, Kirk and his crew must set history back on its correct path...whatever the consequences!
name: Time Crime Part 1

description: In a story set during Dr. Pulaski's tour of duty, Troi is possessed by ancient lifeforms that are draining all power from the Enterprise.
name: Lifesigns

description: As Swamp Thing and Lady Jane commune in the Green, Arcane strikes against Abby. Plus, a bizarre transformation takes place for Dr. Polygon. This issue lays the groundwork for a story that establishes a new direction for Swamp Thing.
name: Cross-Pollination

description: Beginning an exciting new direction for VALOR that will ultimately lead to a major shake-up in the DC Universe. It's a race against time as Valor must return the injured and dying Green Lantern to Oa before Valor's out-of-control powers destroy his ship.
name: Fight The Power

person_credits.name: Roberta Gregory
person_credits.role: writer, editor, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
This is Issue #6 of the comic book series "1963", and features several characters from the entire run of the volume.

The "Tomorrow Syndicate" a superhero team somewhat analogous to The Avengers, go on a mission to find their compatriots "Mystery, Incorporated" whom are inexplicably missing. The team heads into a dimensional opening where it is soon discovered there are alternate realities abound, and the Tomorrow Syndicate end up at a type of way station for superheroes and villains who are traversing from one point in time to the next or who are travelling to other dimensions, realities.

A few parodies of other superhero characters, villains, and concepts abound, and the story sort of flounders around a bit, as the team receives little to no assistance in tracking and finding their friends Mystery, Incorporated. The end of the comic does reveal the identity of the mysterious backwards time traveller whom first appeared in Issue #1 of "1963".
name: From Here To Alternity!

description: Variant: Gold Cover
name: Yellow

description:
Julie and Tilly enjoy a warm summer day, leaving Maxx at home to fix her larmp.

The Savage Dragon has a cameo, and he’s looking for the ‘dangerous psychopath Mako!

Fleeing from the Dragon, Mako burst in on Maxx. Maxx knows he’s no match for the blood thirsty land shark, especially with his claws glued shut. The Maxx is a lousy handyman.

The chase goes on into the night. Mako ends the chase by tackling Maxx into a swimming pool. This causes Maxx to slip into the Outback. There Maxx meets the Leopard Queen again, only this time she appears darker. She inform Maxx that this change is due to Cruelty and pain. We also learn that her Leopard is dead.

The chase continues until they find their way to a phone cord store. Maxx frees his claws with some solvent.

Whit her car broken down Julie finds herself in the Outback where she meets Lil’ Julie. Lil’ Julie tells Julie that she is not part of Maxx;s outback, but the Maxx is part of hers.

She also learns that the Leopard Queen is a part of her.

Dragon defeats DoubleHeader. The Annihilators plot the fall of the Vicious Circle. Mrs. Harris is enraged with Dragon. Emily Schwartzblatt claims Dragon is her son Rodney. Lt. Darling confesses to Dragon, who advises him to run. Freak Force attack the Annihilators. Mighty Man defeats Brawn.

name: Resolution Day

description:
Timothy Halloran has now transformed into Mastodon because of the mRNA process given to him by Malcolm Kort and his scientist Doctor Wendell. Mastodon leaps out of Kort's laboratory in anger to find the Exiles outside. They immediately get into a quick battle due to a quick confusion. Mastodon is able to hold his own against the combined might of the Exiles, with the battle flowing into other areas of the city, most notably a wax museum. Meanwhile, Hot Rox exits Kort's building to find Tinsel and Ghoul hurt on the group, so she captures them and brings them to her boss. Malcolm Kort decides to place Ghoul in with the biological wastes and to leave Tinsel in the placement of Bloodbath. Meanwhile, the other Exiles continue to try to stop Mastodon before he hurts himself or others. Back at the Stronghold, Amber Hunt is determined to undergo the mRNA process to save her life regardless if Doctor Deming is there or not. Doctor Deming's assistant tells Amber not to attempt the process because it is too dangerous. Amber Hunt's argument is that the Theta virus will kill her if she doesn't undergo the process. Ghoul finds himself in the biological wastes compartment and speaks to the souls of Supreme Soviet and others. Before too long, the room is set ablaze and Ghoul is incinerated. Mastodon is able to escape the Exiles and transforms back to him human self, though he is tracked by one of Malcolm Kort's cybernoids. Tinsel awakes in the bedroom of Bloodbath, who is in the middle of undress. He attempts to rape her when she blinds him with her light-based power. Being blind herself, she awkwardly tries to escape but Bloodbath shoots her down, killing her. Ghoul reforms his body, thanks to his ultra ability, and escapes the biological waste department to find Tinsel's dead body. He vows he will avenge her death and he asks her soul who the killer is.

In a back-up story, Rune's origin is revealed.
name: A Glimmer And Gone...

description: The group are chased to ground by a mercenary team that doesn't care if any innocents are hurt in the crossfire.
name: Hounded

description:
The police investigate a new ultra villain named Hardwire, who has the ability to cut things with his fingers on a molecular level. Meanwhile, Hardcase meets with the head of Choice Corporation, Bob Dixon, to get to the bottom of the problem involving chase and the ultras chasing her. Bob Dixon does not relent, but Hardcase informs him that she is under his protection. After that meeting, Rex Mundi indirectly hires Hardwire to take care of Hardcase. Meanwhile, NM-E, the robot that destroyed the Squad, has returns back to life, assimilating a young man to strengthen itself.

A backup story involving Rune is added to this issue and every issue under the Ultraverse banner for the month of October, 1993.
name: Friends And Enemies, Part One: The First Cut

description:
Johnny Domino survives the car accident he suffered through and thanks the doctor who saved his life. When walking home from the hospital, Johnny Domino can hear a man's thoughts that indicate he wants to kill a woman. Alarmed, Johnny believes he may be going crazy because of the hunk of metal that is still embedded in his brain, but decides to investigate this man in case he isn't insane. He follows the man to a restaurant and overhears the man set up a date with the waitress there for the upcoming Saturday. Johnny leaves the area and rushes home to decide what to do where he comes into contact with two burglars. Donning a costume, Johnny Domino defeats the two burglars, proving to himself that he has what it takes to face a killer if he needs to. On that Saturday, Johnny visits the restaurant that the killer form the other day visited and tried to make a date with the same waitress, but she refused due to her prior commitment. However, she informs Johnny that her name is Ginger Robinson and that she is listed in the phone book. Johnny then leaves to visit his father before he goes to Ginger's house as Night Man, to prevent her from being killed. When he sees Ginger, he tries to warn her of the killer but finds that the killer's thoughts are coming from Ginger herself. It takes a few moments for Night Man to learn that the killer has already killed Ginger and has cut her face off, using it as a mask. The killer, now known as Deathmask, escapes on a boat and Night Man follows suit. They battle in the middle of the ocean, where blood that has dropped into the water attracts some sharks. Night Man pushes Deathmask into the water, presumably to his death. While Night Man ponders on a cape to keep himself warm, Deathmask's fist rises past the surface of the water.

In a back-up story, the origin of Rune is revealed.
name: The Night Man

description: Include a preview of Barry Windsor-Smith's Rune.
name: "Villains" / "The Sorcerer"

description: Extreme fights the combined might of the Protectors and the Ex-Mutants. One of the Ex-Mutants, Shannon, arises from a coma and is imbued with massive powers. She is able to fight Extreme to a standstill while Night Mask finds a device to teleport Extreme and his minions back to his dimension. After the battle, a government liaison informs the two super teams that there will a change in their future, with Gravestone and Arc joining the Ex-Mutants and Tanya and Piper joining the Protectors. If that wasn't enough, Philip Reinhart is forced to introduce Chalice, the Protector's new mandated leader.
name: Genesis, Part 6: To Live Or Die In L.A.

description: Prototype battles the Heater
name: Hero and the Terror

description:
The creature, Sludge, climbs out of the sewers in Manhattan right in the middle of some gang members performing a drive-by.

He crushes their car and so they decide to try and kill him. After being shot and stabbed Sludge learns of his healing abilities. Also for rapid cell growth when coming into contact with human skin.

We learn of Sludge's origin, a crooked cop by the name Frank Hoag, who refused to kill another officer of the law. He was pursued through the building and shot up in the lab, and dumped, where the chemicals mixed with his body, giving birth the Sludge.
name: You Can Take The Cop Out Of The Sewer...

description:
The Solution are in Tokyo, Japan to meet with a potential client. The client is a Russian member of the KGB who wants to hire the Solution to solve the problem of Quattro destroying Russian nuclear bases and stealing their warheads. While Tech goes to meet with the client, each member of the Solution go on their own for reconnaissance. Each member is attacked by a member of Quattro. The Solution is able to defeat Quattro and they escape, thanks to their member Gate. In the confusion of battle, the Russian client is killed before he can offer the Solution the job. Shadowmage believes that Quattro will not attack again, but Tech believes they will fight again.

In a back-up story, the origin of Rune is revealed.
name: Showdown
Old Wounds

description:
The Strangers enjoy well-deserved down time, so each member goes back to their personal lives, dealing with their life as an ultra. Atom Bob visits his welcoming family, but a plethora of media surrounds their home. Grenade and Electrocute go to Grenade's home as well, but decides to not entertain the media cameras and instead opt for a walk in the neighborhood, expressing their mutual attraction. Zip Zap returns to his neighborhood and takes care of some gang members that have harassed him for years. Lady Killer returns to her company office to handle some business affairs and the future of the Strangers. Spectral visits a friend in the hospital, hoping his new ultra ability would be able to heal him. Yrial hears a woman screaming in the streets and finds that the woman was on the cable car that changed the Strangers into ultras. The woman, Henrietta Hawkins, claims that someone killed everyone on her block, someone named Deathwish. Yrial contacts the other Strangers to investigate the disturbance. There the Strangers find a trail of corpses that have been reduced to a crumbling, rotting state. That's when Deathwish shows himself, battling the Strangers. The battle seems to be pointless as Deathwish can't be hurt until Spectral arrives. He uses his growing ability to cause Deathwish to explode. Spectral then reveals to the team that he is gay and the friend he tried to save earlier actually died because he advanced his friend's disease as well as his friend's body. The Strangers offer support and unite as friends as well as teammates.

In a back-up story, the origin of Rune is told.
name: Dynamic Tension

description:
The Vision questions whether he can experience love the way his teammates do. While mulling over his past, Deathcry pushes Vision to an emotional breaking point. Is Vision truly the automaton he believes himself to be?

The Vision battles with his struggle to reclaim his emotions. Luna gets kidnapped by Fabian Cortez.

Pin up of Crystal and Quicksilver
name: Voyeuristic Visions

description: In the timeless city of Chronopolis, the battle is joined between Terminatrix’s avengers and Revelation’s avengers! The shield-slinger, golden avenger, and thunder god clash with the three men that at one time or another assumed their identities! And as expected they eventually reach a stalemate and begin searching for their true enemy! However during the fracas, Terminatrix leaps far into the future (beyond Kang’s eight millennia empire) and encounters Marcus Immortus! The new Mistress of Time keeps getting further into trouble! Will she turn back to the Avengers for help?
name: On the Side of the Angels

description: It’s total mayhem as Captain America takes on the mysterious Blazing Skull!
name: Skull Sessions

description: At last, Daredevil comes face-to-face with Eddie, and the truth about the mysterious man's past is revealed! But first, Daredevil will have his hands full with an eerily familiar creature known only as Hellspawn! Meanwhile, the mysterious Snakeroot finally makes its move!
name: Fall From Grace - Part 2: Transgression

description: Young Matt Murdock is the son of Battlin' Jack Murdock, a down-on-his-luck boxer who has been forced to become a mob thug in order to pay his bills. Matt Murdock's life forever changes the day he saves a man from an oncoming truck, becoming blinded by radioactive chemicals. Having his other senses enhanced, Matt begins to see the world in a different way. It is then that Matt is approached by the mysterious Stick, who trains Matt to be a warrior. But unfortunately for Matt, his life is about to change again when his father refuses to take a dive...

Deadpool is captured by the Executive Elite and they go through some old memories. Meanwhile, Copycat has found a trail that leads to Tolliver's will, but she isn't the only one. Deadpool and Weasel beat the Executive Elite and begin their bid for Tolliver's will.

Synopsis

It all starts with Deadpool in a side street. He comes upon Makeshift and Rive. They are there to capture Deadpool. They have Deadpool stuck to the wall, which he doesn’t like. Makeshift shot a weapon at Deadpool’s neck to send voltage through his body. Makeshift and Rive captured Deadpool. Now they had to wait for Comcast to arrive. Makeshift is very impatient. They take Deadpool to “The Edsel”.

The Executive Elite introduce themselves formally to Deadpool. This was mostly for Commcast, since they haven’t met yet. Commcast put a mechanical collar around Deadpool’s neck. Deadpool thought it was for torture.

The comic flashes back to 3 days ago. We see Copycat in Washington DC. She went to see Jacob Gavin Jr. to see if she could get information about Tolliver’s will.

We then come to a flashback from Deadpool. We see him with Vanessa Carlysle, Copycat. He is saying goodbye to her and walked away. Deadpool gets mad because they are in his head.

Commcast thinks Deadpool is furious about the pain from the machine. We see another flashback with Garrison Kane. Deadpool talks about his chemo also.

Deadpool is trying to get out of them giving him to midgets, so Deadpool offered double. Commcast shows the disc that he has. Deadpool then takes his mask off and reveals his messed up face. The Executive Elite team is shocked by the look of his face. At that point Weasel busts in and Deadpool gets loose.

Back to Copycat. She is in Switzerland now trying to get access to Tolliver’s will. She gets mad at the man there because she finds out that someone else has accessed the information before she did.

Deadpool takes out Makeshift and Rive, Weasel takes out Commcast. They now have both discs so they can find out where Tolliver’s will is located. When they get the information pulled up they see where it is and that there might be something there protecting it called “Unit 0”

Copycat gets to the site where Tolliver’s will is supposed to be hidden and is captured by Slayback. They will now wait together for Deadpool so he can kill him.
name: The Circle Chase: Round 3 - ...And Quacks Like a Duck.

description: When the Guardians attempt to liberate the Inhumans, the ungreatful captives tell them to get lost! Composite and several rookie Inhumans battle the Guardians, while Loki's war with Starhawk takes them to 31st Century Asgard, where they meet a certain hammer-weilding 31st Century Asgardian!
name: Too Err Is Inhuman

description:
The Hulk leans an old friend is being treated miserably in prison after being accused of heinous crimes. So, he decides to break in and rescue her. Trouble is, it's an American prison!

Plus: Ulysses Part 4: Out of the Fire.
name: Jailhouse Rock; Ulysses, Part 4: Out of the Fire

description:
After teaming up with Drax The Destroyer to fight Thor, The Hulk is abandoned and left to drift in space above Paradise Omega. Can the Jade Giant make it back to the surface in time to join the action?

The battle of the heroes has begun on the surface of Paradise Omega. As the heroes crash land on the planet they are all assaulted by the Holy Guard.

The Goddess' control over the Holy Guard is great, making most lose their character to battle for her and people who never kill are now trying to end their opponents lives. Almost all the heroes are caught off guard by the Holy Guard and their surprise attacks.

Adam Warlock has finished his business in the Soul World. Thanos transports him to an unknown location.

Thanos fires the Dreadnaught 666 upon the planets surface. he then uses the power of Professor X and the Soul Gem in an attempt to breach the Cosmic Egg and reach the Goddess. He is unable to penetrate her defenses and fails to stop her from fulfilling the final rapture, destroying the entire universe.
name: Holy War!

description: Marlene is regretting her decision to join FalkonCorp while Cruz and Cray sneak through the building in stolen FalkonCorp guard uniforms. They unknowingly trigger an alarm and Seth himself faces them, draining Cray's life-force and leaving Cruz a babbling mess. Meanwhile, Frenchie is being beaten by Agony and Flare in Chloe's apartment. The fights back and is thrown out a window. Hanging from the fire escape, he transforms into Pierre Latrec. Marc learns of the fates of Cray and Cruz and waits until dark to get his revenge. As Pierre Latrec, Frenchie violently fights back, killing Flare and ripping Agony's hair out. At the same time, Moon Knight breaks into FalkonCorp, facing heavy security. He makes it to Seth's office, only to see... himself.
name: Phalkon Corpse

description:
The Surfer has landed! But he's on Paradise Omega, the Goddess's planet, and he's barely alive. And then there's the welcoming committee - Wonder Man and Storm - who wants to make sure that the Surfer never recovers.

Summary
The Silver Surfer has been found on Paradise Omega by two members of the Holy Guard, Storm and Wonder Man. Wonder Man sees the Surfer as a heretic while Storm tries to tell him the Goddess is the way of compassion. Wonder Man beats on the defenseless Silver Surfer until he is satisfied he is finished.

The Surfer's powers return to him and he still continues to plead with them that the Goddess is controlling them. They will not listen and the Surfer attacks. He defeats Wonder Man which angers Storm and makes her change her mind about the Surfer. The Surfer stops her and shows that he is compassionate as well by healing Wonder Man.

He tells them that they must remain enemies and both of them must do as they feel is right. They remain faithful to the Goddess, but choose not to attack the Surfer again.
name: Compassion

description: A reprint of the first appearance of the lizard.
While the Goddess retreats inside her cosmic egg, Moondragon has Spider-Man fight battle within himself.
name: Crisis of Conscience (Part 2 of 3): Soul Gauntlet

description:
When Random sets his sights on Polaris, is he out for blood? Perhaps there are more secrets behind this mysterious vigilante's actions than anyone has suspected...

SPOILERS

Random fights Polaris and Wolfsbane goes nuts....again!
name: Fatal Repulsions

description: Wise Son's family comes to the Dead Zone, just as the Demon Fox begins his/her attack! Plus, Brickhouse is plagued by strange convulsions, and Holocaust returns!
name: Enter The Fox

description: Rocket comes to the aid of the recently pulped Icon, and then, while Icon and the Blood Syndicate engage in Round Two, Rocket goes head to head with Wise Son.
name: IllumiNation

description: Skywise tells the bedtime story of the wishing ring he had as youth.
name: THE WISHING RING

description:
Thor and Drax are in an epic battle in the orbit of Paradise Omega. No matter how much Thor beats on Drax, he always gets up. To top it off, Thor believes Drax's lack of intelligence to be an insult to him. Moondragon contacts Thor and tells him he is needed on the surface. But Thor, will finish his battle. He remembers that he will be the servant to no man or woman, and rejects the Goddess, breaking her grasp on him.

Moondragon informs the Goddess of Thor's betrayal, but the Goddess is not worried. The rapture is minutes away.

Drax and Thor continue to battle but they soon are stopped. They look over to see the sun going nova, consuming and destroying them both.
name: The God and the Brute

description:
Overview

In the hellish heat of New Orleans, the devils meet! In pursuit of a killer, private investigator Mantovani teams up with the mysterious Calhoun, a gambler and a Grendel with a mission of his own. Unbeknownst to them, however, the ferocious Dulac is lying in wait! Meanwhile, both Gloria and Bixby have also arrived in New Orleans -- ready to pay the devil his due!

Summary

The head of the New Orleans Grendel Krewe, Renute, is revealed to be behind the Batiaque killings, and is now searching for woman named Simone and her child.

Alfred reminisces about his life before he went insane, when he was married to a woman named...Simone--before losing her to a gambler. Alfred had a child on his own but the baby died in the jungle.

Mantovani and Calhoun, the gambling Grendel, get together. It turns out that Calhoun knew the Batiaques. They try to track down the black Grendel who attacked Mantovani earlier, and find that his name is Dulac. They capture him. He explains that Renute believes he is related to the ancient French king Charlemagne, and that he will host the reincarnation of the original Grendel, Hunter Rose, if he kills all of Charlemagne's other descendants--including Simone and her child. However, Dulac escapes before they can kill him.

Gloria finds out the Grendel Krewe has the treasure she is seeking, and seduces Radley Benton, the Krewe's local curator.
name: Four Questions, Three Answers

volume.name: Grendel Tales: Four Devils, One Hell

description:
Cerbus, Astoria, Cirin, and Suentus all meet. Victor Reed, who wrote "Reads" goes to a convention to get a publisher. he meets various parodies of publishing companies.

Also contains a 12 page "Chris" preview by Colin Upton
name: Mothers and Daughters 25 : Reads 1
The Measure of the Man

description: Wolverine and Jubilee battle the Sentinels. Then Wolverine talks the Sentinels out taking over the world. Jubilee finds the two men that killed her parents and beats them up.
name: Jubilee's Revenge

description:
Adam Warlock has traveled to the Soul World. He seeks out the Magus.

He asks for the Magus' help in defeating the Goddess. The offer is for them to merge once again. This would give Magus the possibility of taking over Adam's psyche, which has already happened in a past that was erased. But, Magus only hates one thing more than his imprisonment, and that is Adam Warlock.

He attacks Adam with a plan to take Warlock's body and return to reality. But he is no match for Warlock who easily defeats him. Warlock realizes that he does not need the Magus' help, for what help could pure hatred be? He leaves Magus and the Soul World.
name: The Dark Mirror

description:
The 'Reign of the Supermen'. It's do or die (again?) as the Men of Steel invade Mongul's Engine City!

Notes:

  • Green Lantern, Martha and Johnathan Kent cameo appearances.
  • Triangle 1993 #29.
  • Story continues in Green Lantern #46.
  • Chronological continuation from Action Comics #691.
  • Chronological continuation in Superman #82.
name: Blast Off!

description:
Catwoman tracks the assassin that attacked her home to Santa Prisca, where she becomes involved in the island's political scene.

Catwoman is in Santa Prisca, island republic of the Caribbean, on the tracks of the assassin who shattered her life. When she finally finds him, she ends up saving the life of El Jefe Del Pais, the ruler of the island.

In the meantime, in Gotham City, Bane has been taken down by Batman. But this, is a story on its own...

Notes:

  • Special thanks to Frank McLaughlin.
  • Batman, Jean-Paul Valley and Bane cameo flashback appearances.
name: Life Lines: Chapter Three: Shadow of the Cat!

description: Rampage of the Goliath Green Hulk! Spider-Man joins forces with Doc Samson to stop Hulk’s attack in New York. Mary Jane’s acting career hits the skids, while Aunt May vows to uncover the truth behind Peter’s parents!
name: Emerald Rage!

description: Variant: Gold Cover
name: Blue

description: Flash and Francis Kane must work together to keep the bomb from detonating, while Nightwing and Starfire take on the Combine in "Back On Track, Conclusion: Going Out With A Bang!" Part 4 of 4, continued from the previous issue.
name: Back On Track Part 4 of 4: Going Out With A Bang

description: The League is routed, its headquarters in ruins, all at the bidding of the mysterious leader of a worldwide conspiracy of terror. After this adventure, two members leave for good.
name: Inferno!

description: A holodeck adventure, with Picard taking the role of Depression Era private eye Dixon Hill.
name: The Rich and the Dead

description: In the Batroc story, he battles a bank robbery gang led by a little person with psychic powers. Kicks defeat his adversaries, which probably surprises nobody.

description: In Sin City, it's easy to hide from the present, but impossible to forget the past. Frank Miller makes a return trip to Sin City and brings eager readers along for the ride. On the way, meet Dwight, a photographer who specializes in hard-to-get shots... the incriminating kind. The kind that lead to messy, expensive divorces. Dwight's doing his best to forget the past, and was doing a pretty good job until the phone rang. Sin City: A Dame to Kill For #1 is another no-holds-barred, chiaroscuro excursion to the favorite city of Frank Miller, winner of the National Cartoonists' Award for Best Comic Book of 1992. This premiere issue features cover-to-cover story and a special mystery guest.
